msgid "A quadratic Hamiltonian is initialized like so:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/11_quadratic_hamiltonian_and_slater_determinants.ipynb:202
msgid "Diagonalization and state preparation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/11_quadratic_hamiltonian_and_slater_determinants.ipynb:204
msgid "A quadratic Hamiltonian can always be rewritten in the form"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/11_quadratic_hamiltonian_and_slater_determinants.ipynb:206
msgid "H = \\sum_{j} \\varepsilon_j b^\\dagger_j b_j + \\text{constant}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/11_quadratic_hamiltonian_and_slater_determinants.ipynb:211
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\varepsilon_0 \\leq \\varepsilon_1 \\leq \\cdots \\leq "
"\\varepsilon_N` are non-negative real numbers called orbitals energies "
"and the :math:`\\{b_j^\\dagger\\}` are a new set of fermionic creation "
"operators that also satisfy the canonical anticommutation relations. "
"These new creation operators are linear combinations of the original "
"creation and annihilation operators:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/11_quadratic_hamiltonian_and_slater_determinants.ipynb:213
msgid ""
"\\begin{pmatrix}\n"
"b^\\dagger_1 \\\\\n"
"\\vdots \\\\\n"
"b^\\dagger_N \\\\\n"
"\\end{pmatrix}\n"
"= W\n"
"\\begin{pmatrix}\n"
"a^\\dagger_1 \\\\\n"
"\\vdots \\\\\n"
"a^\\dagger_N \\\\\n"
"a_1 \\\\\n"
"\\vdots \\\\\n"
"a_N\n"
"\\end{pmatrix},"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/11_quadratic_hamiltonian_and_slater_determinants.ipynb:231
msgid ""
"where :math:`W` is an :math:`N \\times 2N` matrix. Given a basis of "
"eigenvectors of the Hamiltonian, each eigenvector is labeled by a subset "
"of :math:`\\{0, \\ldots, N - 1\\}`, which we call the occupied orbitals. "
"The corresponding eigenvalue is the sum of the corresponding values of "
":math:`\\varepsilon_j`, plus the constant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/11_quadratic_hamiltonian_and_slater_determinants.ipynb:291
msgid ""
"The transformation matrix :math:`W` is used to construct a circuit to "
"prepare an eigenvector of the Hamiltonian. The circuit is constructed "
"using the ``FermionicGaussianState`` class. Currently, only the `Jordan-"
"Wigner Transform "
"<https://qiskit.org/documentation/nature/stubs/qiskit_nature.second_q.mappers.JordanWignerMapper.html>`__"
" is supported. The circuit for the Jordan-Wigner Transform has linear "
"depth and uses only linear qubit connectivity. The algorithm is from "
"`Phys. Rev.Â Applied 9, 044036 "
"<https://journals.aps.org/prapplied/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevApplied.9.044036>`__."
msgstr ""

